The paper deals with a problem related to preprocessing a string of length n and finding distinct elements whose relative frequencies in a given range are more than a threshold. This problem is related to data structures and algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the space and time complexity of the solution, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of finding range majorities and minorities is also related to data mining (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of space usage, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
